wfBacPktGenDelete.name: wfBacPktGenDelete
wfBacPktGenDelete.description: Create/Delete parameter. Default is created. Users perform a set operation on this object in order to create/delete BAC PktGen.

wfBacPktGenDisable.name: wfBacPktGenDisable
wfBacPktGenDisable.description: Enable/Disable parameter. Default is disabled. Users perform a set operation on this object in order to enable/disable BAC PktGen.

wfBacPktGenState.name: wfBacPktGenState
wfBacPktGenState.description: The current state of the entire BAC PktGen: up - BAC PktGen is sending and receiving frames; down - BAC PktGen is disabled; init - BAC PktGen is initializing; notpresent - BAC PktGen is not present.

wfBacPktGenTxTabSum.name: wfBacPktGenTxTabSum
wfBacPktGenTxTabSum.description: Total number of TXTAB records added to CXP's.

wfBacPktGenRxTabSum.name: wfBacPktGenRxTabSum
wfBacPktGenRxTabSum.description: Total number of RXTAB records added to CXP's.

wfBacPktGenCxpTable.name: wfBacPktGenCxpTable
wfBacPktGenCxpTable.description: The BAC PktGen CXP table contains relevant information concerning packet generation on each CXP. Note that, the processing of PktGen CXP entries supercedes that of wfBacPktGenCxpGlobal MIB record.

wfBacPktGenCxpEntry.name: wfBacPktGenCxpEntry
wfBacPktGenCxpEntry.description: Information concerning packet generation on the CXP.

wfBacPktGenCxpDelete.name: wfBacPktGenCxpDelete
wfBacPktGenCxpDelete.description: Create/Delete parameter. Default is created. Users perform a set operation on this object in order to create/delete BAC PktGen CXP table entry.

wfBacPktGenCxpId.name: wfBacPktGenCxpId
wfBacPktGenCxpId.description: Uniquely identifies the CXP from which test packets are generated. Currently, the CXP is identified by its slot number, which must be between 6 and 8.

wfBacPktGenStreamMask.name: wfBacPktGenStreamMask
wfBacPktGenStreamMask.description: Bit mask for generating test packets on the CXP streams 1-31. The least significant bit is ignored. The second least significant bit represents stream 1, the next least significant bit represents stream 2, and so forth. The most significant bit represents stream 31.

wfBacPktGenSeedPkts.name: wfBacPktGenSeedPkts
wfBacPktGenSeedPkts.description: Seed/Unseed packet parameter. Default is unseedpackets. Users perform a set operation on this object in order to seed/unseed test packets.

wfBacPktGenPktSeedState.name: wfBacPktGenPktSeedState
wfBacPktGenPktSeedState.description: Based on the set operation performed on the Seed/Unseed packet parameter, this object reflects the status of the operation. Default is idle. This object goes to the operationstarted state as soon as the BAC PktGen application detects the set operation on the Seed/Unseed parameter. The object remains in this state until the operation is completed, and the appropriate state is registered.

wfBacPktGenCxpGlobalDelete.name: wfBacPktGenCxpGlobalDelete
wfBacPktGenCxpGlobalDelete.description: Create/Delete parameter. Default is created. Users perform a set operation on this object in order to create/delete BAC PktGen CXP Global record. Note that, the PktGen Global record is processed as long as no wfBacPktGenCxpEntry MIB records exist. When one or more wfBacPktGenCxpEntry MIB records are configured, the PktGen CXP Global record is ignored and its processing is disabled.

wfBacPktGenGlobalStreamMask.name: wfBacPktGenGlobalStreamMask
wfBacPktGenGlobalStreamMask.description: Bit mask for generating test packets on all CXP streams 1-31. The least significant bit is ignored. The second least significant bit represents stream 1, the next least significant bit represents stream 2, and so forth. The most significant bit represents stream 31.

wfBacPktGenGlobalRecActive.name: wfBacPktGenGlobalRecActive
wfBacPktGenGlobalRecActive.description: Indicates if the processing of this MIB record is active. It is active only when NO wfBacPktGenCxpEntry MIB record is configured.

wfBacPktGenCctEntry.name: wfBacPktGenCctEntry
wfBacPktGenCctEntry.description: Information concerning a BAC PktGen circuit table entry.

wfBacPktGenCctDelete.name: wfBacPktGenCctDelete
wfBacPktGenCctDelete.description: Create/Delete parameter. Default is created. Users perform a set operation on this object in order to create/delete BAC PktGen Circuit table entry.

wfBacPktGenCctState.name: wfBacPktGenCctState
wfBacPktGenCctState.description: The current state of the BAC PktGen circuit: up - The circuit is up; down - The circuit is down; init - The circuit is initializing; notpresent - The circuit is not present.

wfBacPktGenPktFileAppend.name: wfBacPktGenPktFileAppend
wfBacPktGenPktFileAppend.description: Append disable/enable parameter. Default is to release previous table contents instead of appending to previously processed pkt files. This feature is currently not supported.

wfBacPktGenPktFileName.name: wfBacPktGenPktFileName
wfBacPktGenPktFileName.description: The user-defined name of the pktfile to process.

wfBacPktGenPktGrpTable.name: wfBacPktGenPktGrpTable
wfBacPktGenPktGrpTable.description: The BAC PktGen packet group table.

wfBacPktGenPktGrpEntry.name: wfBacPktGenPktGrpEntry
wfBacPktGenPktGrpEntry.description: Information concerning a BAC PktGen packet group table entry.

wfBacPktGenPktGrpNumber.name: wfBacPktGenPktGrpNumber
wfBacPktGenPktGrpNumber.description: Uniquely identifies the packet group number.

wfBacPktGenPktGrpDelay1.name: wfBacPktGenPktGrpDelay1
wfBacPktGenPktGrpDelay1.description: Delay parameter 1 for this packet group.

wfBacPktGenPktGrpDelay2.name: wfBacPktGenPktGrpDelay2
wfBacPktGenPktGrpDelay2.description: Delay parameter 2 for this packet group.

wfBacPktGenPktGrpDelay3.name: wfBacPktGenPktGrpDelay3
wfBacPktGenPktGrpDelay3.description: Delay parameter 3 for this packet group.

wfBacPktGenPktGrpDelay4.name: wfBacPktGenPktGrpDelay4
wfBacPktGenPktGrpDelay4.description: Delay parameter 4 for this packet group.

wfBacPktGenPktGrpCount1.name: wfBacPktGenPktGrpCount1
wfBacPktGenPktGrpCount1.description: Count parameter 1 for this packet group.

wfBacPktGenPktGrpCount2.name: wfBacPktGenPktGrpCount2
wfBacPktGenPktGrpCount2.description: Count parameter 2 for this packet group.

wfBacPktGenPktGrpCount3.name: wfBacPktGenPktGrpCount3
wfBacPktGenPktGrpCount3.description: Count parameter 3 for this packet group.

wfBacPktGenPktGrpCount4.name: wfBacPktGenPktGrpCount4
wfBacPktGenPktGrpCount4.description: Count parameter 4 for this packet group.

wfBacPktGenPktSeedSum.name: wfBacPktGenPktSeedSum
wfBacPktGenPktSeedSum.description: Total number of packet seeds that belong to this packet group.

wfBacPktGenPktGrpCxp.name: wfBacPktGenPktGrpCxp
wfBacPktGenPktGrpCxp.description: The eligible CXP slot number on which this packet group can be thrown.

wfBacPktGenStrmCtrlTable.name: wfBacPktGenStrmCtrlTable
wfBacPktGenStrmCtrlTable.description: The BAC PktGen stream control table.

wfBacPktGenStrmCtrlEntry.name: wfBacPktGenStrmCtrlEntry
wfBacPktGenStrmCtrlEntry.description: Information concerning a BAC PktGen stream control table entry.

wfBacPktGenStrmNumber.name: wfBacPktGenStrmNumber
wfBacPktGenStrmNumber.description: Uniquely identifies the PktGen stream number on each CXP.

wfBacPktGenStrmState.name: wfBacPktGenStrmState
wfBacPktGenStrmState.description: The current state of this PktGen stream: pktgen - Stream is transmitting test packets; killed - Stream is being killed; notpresent - Stream is not present.

wfBacPktGenSetStrmPktGrp.name: wfBacPktGenSetStrmPktGrp
wfBacPktGenSetStrmPktGrp.description: Set the packet group to be thrown by this PktGen stream.

wfBacPktGenStrmPktGrp.name: wfBacPktGenStrmPktGrp
wfBacPktGenStrmPktGrp.description: The packet group which will be thrown by this PktGen stream.
